  • Agra

Agra is a city in the northern state of Uttar Pradesh, India. It is a major tourist destination for its many Mughal-era buildings such as Taj Mahal Agra Fort.

  • Rajasthan

Rajasthan is known for its historical hills forts & palaces, it is claimed as the best place for tourism-related to palaces.

  • New Delhi

New Delhi is the capital of India and an administrative district of NCT Delhi. Delhi is famous for its garden of five senses which have made it popular among nature lovers.

  • Mumbai

Mumbai offers natural heritage and modern entertainment including leisure spots, beaches, cinemas, studios, holy places and historical monuments.

  • Amritsar

Amritsar is the largest and most important city in Punjab and is a major commercial, cultural and transportation center. It is famous for its beautiful Golden Temple. 

  • Tirupati

Tirupati is a city in the Indian state of Andhra Pradesh. Its Sri Venkateswara Temple sits atop one of the 7 peaks of Tirumala Hills ,attracting scores of Hindu pilgrims.
